README.md

Awesome

   A collaborative list of great resources about RESTful API architecture,
   development, test, and performance. Feel free to contribute to this
   on-going list.
     * Design
     * Standards
     * Clients
          + PHP
          + Client-side JavaScript
          + Node.js
          + Ruby
          + Go
     * Servers
          + Directly On Top Of A RMDB
          + Node.js
          + PHP
          + Symfony2
          + Python
          + Ruby
          + Go
          + Java
          + Haskell
     * Testing
          + Querying
          + Mocking
          + Public REST APIs To Use
            In Tests
     * [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-rest#
       documentation]Documentation
     * [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-rest#
       saas-tools]SaaS Tools
     * [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-rest#
       miscellaneous]Miscellaneous

Design

     * [https://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Efielding/pubs/dissertation/top.htm]Arch
       itectural Styles and the Design of Network-based Software
       Architectures - Roy Fielding's dissertation defining REST
     * [https://github.com/interagent/http-api-design]HTTP API design
       guide extracted from work on the Heroku Platform API
     * [http://www.vinaysahni.com/best-practices-for-a-pragmatic-restful-a
       pi]Best Practices for Designing a Pragmatic RESTful API
     * [http://blog.octo.com/en/design-a-rest-api/]How to design a REST
       API? - Full guide tackling security, pagination, filtering,
       versioning, partial answers, CORS, etc.
     * [http://martinfowler.com/articles/richardsonMaturityModel.html]Rich
       ardson Maturity Model - Explained by Martin Fowler, originally
       presented by Leonard Richardson at the
       [https://www.crummy.com/writing/speaking/2008-QCon/act3.html]QCon
       2008.
     * [http://martinfowler.com/articles/enterpriseREST.html]Enterprise
       Integration Using REST - Discusses the constraints and flexibility
       that you have with nonpublic APIs, and lessons learned from doing
       large scale RESTful integration across multiple teams.
     * [http://timelessrepo.com/haters-gonna-hateoas]HATEOAS - Clear
       explanation on what HATEOAS is, and why you should use it.
     * [http://www.infoq.com/articles/webber-rest-workflow/]How to GET a
       cup of coffee
     * [http://www.restapitutorial.com/]REST API Tutorial -
       RestApiTutorial.com is dedicated to tracking REST API best
       practices and making resources available to enable quick reference
       and self education for the development crafts-person.
     * [https://github.com/Microsoft/api-guidelines/blob/vNext/Guidelines.
       md#readme]Microsoft REST API Guidelines - The Microsoft REST API
       Guidelines, as a design principle, encourages application
       developers to have resources accessible to them via a RESTful HTTP
       interface.
     * [https://github.com/shieldfy/API-Security-Checklist]API-Security-Ch
       ecklist - Best practices about REST API security

Standards

     * [http://jsonapi.org/]JSON API - Standard for building APIs in JSON.
     * [http://raml.org/]RAML - Simple and succinct way to describe
       RESTful API.
     * [http://labs.omniti.com/labs/jsend]JSend - Simple specification
       that lays down some rules for how JSON responses from web servers
       should be formatted.
     * [http://www.odata.org/]OData - Open protocol to allow the creation
       and consumption of queryable and interoperable RESTful APIs. Quite
       complex.
     * [http://stateless.co/hal_specification.html]HAL - Simple format
       that gives a consistent and easy way to hyperlink between resources
       in your API (see:
       [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-rest#
       hateoas]HATEOAS).
     * [http://json-ld.org/]JSON-LD - Standard for describing Linked Data
       and hypermedia relations in JSON (W3C).
     * [http://www.hydra-cg.com/]Hydra - Vocabulary for Hypermedia-Driven
       Web APIs (W3C).
     * [http://schema.org/]Schema.org - Collection of schemas describing
       common data models.
     * [https://openapis.org/]OpenAPI - Formerly known as the Swagger
       Specification, OpenAPI specifcation is the world's most popular
       description format for defining Restful APIs.

Clients

PHP Clients

     * [http://guzzle.readthedocs.org/en/latest/]Guzzle - HTTP client and
       framework for consuming RESTful web services.
     * [https://github.com/kriswallsmith/buzz]Buzz - Another lightweight
       HTTP client.
     * [https://github.com/Mashape/unirest-php]unirest for PHP -
       Simplified, lightweight HTTP client library.

JavaScript Clients

     * [https://github.com/mgonto/restangular]restangular - AngularJS
       service to handle REST API properly and easily.
     * [https://github.com/marmelab/restful.js]restful.js - JS client for
       interacting with server-side RESTful resources.
     * [https://github.com/basti1302/traverson]traverson - A Hypermedia
       API/HATEOAS Client for Node.js and the Browser
     * [https://github.com/mulesoft/raml-client-generator]raml-client-gene
       rator - Generates static client libs for js.

Node.js Clients

     * [https://github.com/danwrong/restler]restler - REST client library
       for node.js.
     * [https://github.com/Mashape/unirest-nodejs]unirest for Node.js -
       Simplified, lightweight HTTP client library.

Ruby Clients

     * [https://github.com/rest-client/rest-client]RESTClient - Simple
       HTTP and REST client for Ruby, inspired by microframework syntax
       for specifying actions.
     * [https://github.com/balvig/spyke]Spyke - Interact with REST
       services in an ActiveRecord-like manner.
     * [https://github.com/excon/excon]excon - Usable, fast, simple Ruby
       HTTP 1.1. It works great as a general HTTP(s) client and is
       particularly well suited to usage in API clients.
     * [https://github.com/jnunemaker/httparty]httparty - Makes HTTP fun
       again!
     * [http://ruby-doc.org/stdlib/libdoc/net/http/rdoc/Net/HTTP.html]Net:
       :HTTP - Net::HTTP provides a rich library which can be used to
       build HTTP user-agents.
     * [https://github.com/zlx/raml-ruby-client-generator]raml-ruby-client
       -generator - Auto generate API client from a RAML file.

Go Clients

     * [https://github.com/bndr/gopencils]gopencils - Small and simple
       package to easily consume REST APIs.
     * [https://github.com/go-resty/resty]resty - Simple HTTP and REST
       client for Go inspired by Ruby rest-client.

Servers

Directly On Top Of A RMDB

     * [https://github.com/begriffs/postgrest]postgrest - Serve a fully
       RESTful API directly from an existing PostgreSQL database.
     * [http://blog.ulf-wendel.de/2014/mysql-5-7-http-plugin-mysql/]MySQL
       HTTP plugin - Simple REST-like / CRUD server for any MySQL
       database.
     * [https://github.com/prest/prest]pREST - A fully RESTful API from
       any existing PostgreSQL database written in Go.

Node.js

     * [https://github.com/restify/node-restify]node-restify - Framework
       specifically meant for REST API.
     * [http://sailsjs.org/]Sails.js - Node.js Web framework embedding a
       command to generate automatically a REST API.
     * [https://github.com/jspears/mers]mers - Express service exposing
       Mongoose finders as RESTful API.
     * [https://github.com/wprl/baucis]Baucis - Build scalable REST API
       based on your Mongoose entities.
     * [https://github.com/flatiron/resourceful]flatiron/resourceful -
       Isomorphic Resource engine for JavaScript.
     * [http://loopback.io/]loopback - Powerful Node.js framework for
       creating APIs and easily connecting to backend data sources.
     * [http://feathersjs.com/]Feathers - is a real-time, micro-service
       web framework that gives you control over your data via RESTful
       resources, sockets and flexible plug-ins.
     * [https://github.com/thomas4019/expressa]Expressa - Express
       middleware for creating APIs from JSON schemas with a simple admin
       editor and permissions model.

PHP

     * [https://github.com/marmelab/microrest.php]Microrest - Micro-web
       application providing a REST API on top of any relational database.
     * [https://github.com/willdurand/Negotiation]Negotiation - Content
       negotiation library.
     * [https://github.com/leedavis81/drest]Drest - Library for exposing
       Doctrine entities as REST resource endpoints.
     * [https://github.com/Luracast/Restler]Restler - Lightweight
       framework to expose PHP methods as RESTful web API.
     * [https://github.com/blongden/hal]HAL - Hypertext Application
       Language (HAL) builder library.
     * [https://github.com/zfcampus/zf-apigility-skeleton]Apigility - API
       builder built with Zend Framework 2.
     * [https://github.com/phprest/phprest]phprest - Specialized REST
       microframework for PHP.
     * [https://github.com/willdurand/Hateoas]Hateoas - PHP library to
       support implementing representations for HATEOAS REST web services.
     * [https://github.com/apioo/fusio]Fusio - Open source API management
       platform.

Symfony2

     * [http://williamdurand.fr/2012/08/02/rest-apis-with-symfony2-the-rig
       ht-way/]REST APIs with Symfony2: the Right Way - Complete guide to
       build a state-of-the-art REST API with Symfony2 framework.
     * [https://github.com/FriendsOfSymfony/FOSRestBundle]FOSRestBundle -
       Bundle handling view, routing, error handling, etc. for your REST
       API.
     * [https://github.com/stanlemon/rest-bundle]stanlemon/rest-bundle -
       Build a REST API based on Doctrine entities using conventions over
       configuration.
     * [http://lakion.com/lionframe]lakion/Lionframe - Glu between several
       community libraries to ease API development.
     * [https://github.com/willdurand/BazingaHateoasBundle]BazingaHateoasB
       undle - Integrate the
       [https://github.com/willdurand/Hateoas]Hateoas library into a
       Symfony2 application.
     * [https://github.com/gimler/symfony-rest-edition]Symfony REST
       Edition - Start with a Symfony2 application with all REST-friendly
       bundles pre-configured.
     * [https://github.com/marmelab/NgAdminGeneratorBundle]NgAdminGenerato
       rBundle - Boostrap ng-admin configuration based on
       stanlemon/rest-bundle.
     * [https://github.com/dunglas/DunglasApiBundle]DunglasApiBundle -
       Build a REST API which follow Hydra/JSON-LD specification.
     * [https://github.com/api-platform/api-platform]API Platform -
       Specialize Symfony edition for the creation of hypermedia REST
       APIs.
     * [https://github.com/nelmio/NelmioApiDocBundle]NelmioApiDocBundle -
       Generate documentation for your REST API from annotations.

Python

     * [http://www.django-rest-framework.org/]Django REST framework -
       Powerful and flexible toolkit that makes it easy to build Web APIs.
     * [http://tastypieapi.org/]django-tastypie - Creating delicious APIs
       for Django apps.
     * [http://flask-restful.readthedocs.org/]flask-restful - Extension
       for Flask that adds support for quickly building REST APIs.
     * [https://flask-restless.readthedocs.org/en/latest/]flask-restless -
       Flask extension for generating ReSTful APIs for database models
       defined with SQLAlchemy (or Flask-SQLAlchemy).
     * [http://www.hug.rest/]hug - Lightweight and fast API Framework.
     * [https://github.com/jeffknupp/sandman]sandman - Automated REST APIs
       for existing database-driven systems.
     * [http://restless.readthedocs.org/en/latest/]restless - Framework
       agnostic REST framework based on lessons learned from TastyPie.
     * [https://github.com/RueLaLa/savory-pie/]savory-pie - REST API
       building library (django, and others).
     * [http://python-eve.org/]Python Eve - Eve is an open source Python
       REST API framework designed for human beings. It allows to
       effortlessly build and deploy highly customizable, fully featured
       RESTful Web Services.
     * [https://ramses.readthedocs.org/en/stable/]Ramses - Makes RAML
       files executable by generating production-ready APIs from them at
       runtime.
     * [https://github.com/biosustain/potion]Flask-Potion - Flask-Potion
       is a powerful Flask extension for building RESTful JSON APIs. It
       also provides several Clients for easier access to the API.
     * [https://github.com/encode/apistar]apistar - A smart Web API
       framework, designed for Python 3.

Ruby

     * [http://www.ruby-grape.org/]Grape - Opinionated micro-framework for
       creating REST-like APIs in Ruby.
     * [http://guides.rubyonrails.org/api_app.html]Rails - RailsGuides:
       Using Rails for API-only applications.

Go

     * [https://github.com/manishrjain/gocrud]gocrud: Go library to
       simplify creating, updating and deleting arbitrary depth structured
       data -- to make building REST services fast and easy.
     * [https://github.com/ant0ine/go-json-rest]go-json-rest - Thin layer
       on top of net/http that helps building RESTful APIs easily.
     * [https://github.com/dougblack/sleepy]sleepy - RESTful
       micro-framework written in Go.
     * [https://github.com/yookoala/restit]restit - Go micro framework to
       help writing RESTful API integration test.
     * [https://github.com/codehack/go-relax]go-relax - Framework of
       pluggable components to build RESTful API's.
     * [https://github.com/ungerik/go-rest]go-rest - Small and evil REST
       framework for Go.
     * [https://github.com/emicklei/go-restful]go-restful - A declarative
       highly readable framework for building restful API's.
     * [https://github.com/bahlo/goat]Goat - Minimalistic REST API server
       in Go.
     * [https://github.com/resoursea/api]Resoursea - REST framework for
       quickly writing resource based services.
     * [https://github.com/cosiner/zerver]Zerver - Zerver is a expressive,
       modular, feature completed RESTful framework.

Java

     * [https://github.com/RestExpress/RestExpress]RestExpress -
       Netty-based, highly performant, lightweight, container-less,
       plugin-extensible, framework that is ideal for microservice
       architectures.
     * [https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web]Vertx-Web - Vert.x-Web is a
       set of building blocks for building web applications with Vert.x, a
       toolkit for building reactive applications on the JVM.
     * [https://github.com/dropwizard/dropwizard]Dropwizard - A framework
       for developing ops-friendly, high-performance, RESTful web
       services.

Haskell

     * [https://github.com/silkapp/rest]Rest for Haskell - This package
       allows you to create REST APIs in Haskell. These APIs can be run in
       different web frameworks. They can also be used to automatically
       generate documentation as well as client libraries.

Testing

Querying

     * [https://www.hurl.it/]Hurl.it - Make HTTP requests with a simple
       web-based HTTP client -- like curl in the cloud.
     * [https://github.com/jkbrzt/httpie]httpie - Command line HTTP
       client, far more dev-friendly than curl.
     * [https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/postman-rest-client/fdmm
       gilgnpjigdojojpjoooidkmcomcm]Postman REST Client - Chrome extension
       essential to test manually REST API.
     * [https://github.com/micha/resty]resty - Little command line REST
       client that you can use in pipelines (bash or zsh).
     * [https://github.com/stedolan/jq]jq - Command line JSON processor,
       to use in combination with a command-line HTTP client like cURL.
     * [http://www.httpmaster.net/]HttpMaster - GUI tool for testing REST
       APIs and services. Windows OS only.
     * [https://github.com/cloudhead/http-console]Http-console - Command
       line interface for HTTP that let you speak HTTP like a local
     * [https://github.com/rest-assured/rest-assured]rest-assured - Java
       DSL for easy testing of REST services.

Mocking

     * [http://requestb.in/]RequestBin - Inspect and debug webhook
       requests sent by your clients or third-party APIs.
     * [http://httpbin.org/]httpbin - HTTP request and response service -
       a/k/a Swiss Army Knife for HTTP.
     * [https://github.com/marmelab/FakeRest]FakeRest - Patch
       XMLHttpRequest to fake a REST API client-side.
     * [https://github.com/typicode/json-server]json-server - Serve a REST
       API from fixture files using quick prototyping.
     * [http://www.mocky.io/]Mocky.io - Free online service to create fake
       HTTP responses.
     * [https://github.com/bulkismaslom/swagger-api-mock]Swagger API Mock
       - Mock RESTful API based on swagger schema
     * [https://github.com/darklynx/request-baskets]Request Baskets -
       Service to collect HTTP requests and inspect them via RESTful API
       or web UI.
     * [https://github.com/iridakos/duckrails]DuckRails - Mock quickly &
       dynamically API endpoints.

Public REST APIs To Use In Tests

     * [http://deckofcardsapi.com/]Deck of Cards API - Open API for
       simulating a deck of cards.
     * [http://www.programmableweb.com/apis/directory]ProgrammableWeb -
       The world's largest API repository.
     * [https://www.publicapis.com/]Public APIS - Explore The Largest API
       Directory In The Galaxy.
     * [http://developer.marvel.com/]Marvel Comics API - Query characters,
       stories, events about Marvel superheroes.
     * [http://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/]JSON Placeholder - Free
       online REST service that you can use whenever you need some fake
       data.
     * [http://APIs.guru/]APIs.guru - Wikipedia for Web APIs, each API has
       OpenAPI/Swagger description.

Documentation

     * [http://swagger.io/]Swagger - Documentation/querying web interface
       for REST APIs.
     * [http://apidocjs.com/]API doc - Inline Documentation for RESTful
       web APIs.
     * [https://github.com/raml2html/raml2html]raml2html - Generates HTML
       documentation from a RAML file.
     * [https://github.com/Rebilly/ReDoc/]ReDoc - OpenAPI/Swagger-powered
       three-panel documentation.
     * [https://github.com/lord/slate]Slate - Beautiful and responsive
       three-panel API documentation using Middleman.

SaaS tools

     * [https://www.runscope.com/]Runscope - Automated API Monitoring &
       Testing.
     * [https://ping-api.com/]Ping-API - Automated API Monitoring &
       Testing.
     * [https://magic.import.io/]import.io Magic - Create a REST API from
       any website in one click.
     * [https://apiary.io/]Apiary - Collaborative design, instant API
       mock, generated documentation, integrated code samples, debugging
       and automated testing.
     * [https://aws.amazon.com/api-gateway/]Amazon API Gateway - Amazon
       API Gateway is a fully managed service that makes it easy for
       developers to create, publish, maintain, monitor, and secure APIs
       at any scale.
     * [https://apigee.com/]Apigee - Apigee is the leading provider of API
       technology and services for enterprises and developers.
     * [https://assertible.com/]Assertible - Continuously test and monitor
       your APIs after deployments and across environments.
     * [https://www.moesif.com/]Moesif - API Analytics for Debugging,
       Monitoring, and Usage Tracking for RESTful and GraphQL.

Miscellaneous

     * [https://github.com/marmelab/ng-admin]ng-admin - Add an AngularJS
       admin GUI to any RESTful API.
     * [https://github.com/marmelab/admin-on-rest]admin-on-rest - Add a
       ReactJS admin GUI to any RESTful API.
     * [https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-codegen]swagger-codegen -
       Auto generation of client libraries or server stubs given an
       OpenAPI specification (formerly known as the Swagger
       Specification).
     * [https://github.com/ForestAdmin/lumber]Lumber - Generate the admin
       interface of your application.

